item.title: Whats a cache?
item.dc:creator: @Xbox_Modder Xbox Modder
item.description:
@Xbox_Modder wrote:

A cache is where all the information is stored about the items like where the pictures of the items are stored the way the character looks the way a wall looks…

etc

And when you edit your client.java and stuff your adding a code which uses the cache…

It’s kinda hard to explain…

Read full topic

item.title: Whats a cache?
item.dc:creator: @O_M_G1 O M G
item.description:
@O_M_G1 wrote:

The cache is all the ‘pictures’ of RuneScape. The client loads them. Some people have been succesfull at cache editing, thus allowing them to edit how objects look.
